Key Modbus Registers (Holding/Input) 
1. Real-time Monitoring (Input Registers) 
These registers are commonly used for reading current status. 
Register (Hex) 	Description	Units/Scale
3000-3024	General System Data	Various
3000	Status	(0: waiting, 1: checking, 3: normal, 4: fault)
3001	PV1 Voltage	0.1V
3003	PV2 Voltage	0.1V
3005	Total Active Power (Combined 3005/3006)	0.1W
3013	Grid Frequency	0.01Hz
3014-3016	Grid Voltage (L1, L2, L3)	0.1V
3017-3019	Grid Current (L1, L2, L3)	0.1A
3020	PV Power	0.1W
3021-3023	Output Active Power (L1, L2, L3)	0.1W
3024	Reactive Power	0.1var
3025-3026	Total Energy Export to Grid	0.1kWh
3027-3028	Total Energy Import from Grid	0.1kWh
3029-3030	Today Generation Energy	0.1kWh
3031-3032	Total Generation Energy	0.1kWh
2. APX Battery Specific Data (Storage/Hybrid Type) 
These are typically available in the higher register ranges for MOD TL3-XH. 
Symcon Community
Symcon Community
Register (Dec) 	Description	Units/Scale
1000	Battery Status	(0: standby, 1: discharge, 2: charge)
1001	Battery Percentage (SOC)	0.1%
1002	Battery Voltage	0.1V
1003	Battery Power (Discharge/Charge)	0.1W (Signed)
1004	Battery SOC	0.1% (Same as 1001)
1005	Battery Current	0.1A (Signed)
1006	Battery Temperature	0.1Â°C
1007	Battery SoH (Health)	0.1%
3. Configuration & Control (Holding Registers)
Register (Dec) 	Description	Allowed Values/Notes
22	Baud Rate Set	0: 9600, 1: 19200
100	Inverter On/Off	0: Off, 1: On
300	Maximum Active Power	0-100%
400	Battery Charge Priority	Time slot settings (1, 2, 3)